title: Florida Extent of The 100,000 Meter, Florida, 2007
name: Florida Extent of The 100,000 Meter, Florida, 2007
description: This layer represents a 100,000 by 100,000 meter United States National Grid (USNG) for the State of Florida. The USNG is an alpha-numeric reference system based on the UTM coordinate system and is similar to the Military Grid Reference System. Use of the USNG ensures a uniform grid mapping and positional reporting system for search and rescue, emergency planning, response, and recovery.
